---
import LegalPageShell from '../../../components/legal/LegalPageShell.astro';
import {
  slimefallArcadeLegal,
  slimefallArcadePrivacyPolicyUrl,
} from '../../../data/slimefallArcadeLegal';
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const supportHref = `mailto:${slimefallArcadeLegal.supportEmail}`;
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`${slimefallArcadeLegal.appName} Privacy Policy`}
  description={`Privacy policy for ${slimefallArcadeLegal.appName}, including local game data, platform leaderboards, and Google AdMob disclosures.`}
  canonicalUrl={slimefallArcadePrivacyPolicyUrl}
>
  <LegalPageShell
    eyebrow="Privacy Policy"
    title={`Privacy policy for ${slimefallArcadeLegal.appName}`}
    summary={`This policy explains how ${slimefallArcadeLegal.publisher} and third-party platform services handle information when you play ${slimefallArcadeLegal.appName}.`}
    metaItems={[
      { label: 'Effective date', value: slimefallArcadeLegal.effectiveDate },
      { label: 'Publisher', value: slimefallArcadeLegal.publisher },
      {
        label: 'Privacy contact',
        value: slimefallArcadeLegal.supportEmail,
        href: supportHref,
      },
    ]}
    relatedLinks={slimefallArcadeLegal.thirdPartyLinks}
    footerNote={`Public privacy policy for ${slimefallArcadeLegal.appName}. Effective ${slimefallArcadeLegal.effectiveDate}.`}
  >
    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        {slimefallArcadeLegal.appName} is a game for Android and Apple devices.
        The publisher does not require or operate a first-party user account,
        backend profile database, or analytics service for the current release.
        The game uses device-local storage, optional platform leaderboard
        services, and Google AdMob advertising as described below.
      </p>
      <div class="legal-callout">
        The publisher does not sell your personal information.
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Information stored on your device</h2>
      <p>
        The game saves information locally so that play can continue between
        sessions. This information is not sent to the publisher.
      </p>
      <ul>
        {slimefallArcadeLegal.localData.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Platform and advertising services</h2>
      <p>
        If you use rankings or view an advertisement, Google or Apple may
        process information under their own privacy policies. The categories
        involved depend on your device, region, account, consent choices, and
        privacy settings.
      </p>
      <ul>
        {slimefallArcadeLegal.platformData.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
      </ul>
      <p>
        AdMob uses this information to request, deliver, limit, personalize or
        measure ads, maintain ad security, prevent fraud, and diagnose service
        problems. Ads may be personalized, non-personalized, or limited where
        required by your choices, platform settings, or applicable law.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>How information is used</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Save game progress and preferences on the device.</li>
        <li>Authenticate an optional platform gaming profile.</li>
        <li>Submit scores and display native leaderboards.</li>
        <li>Deliver rewarded and interstitial advertisements.</li>
        <li>Protect advertising services against abuse and technical failures.</li>
        <li>Respond when you voluntarily send a support or privacy email.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Retention and deletion</h2>
      <p>
        Local game information remains on your device until it is overwritten,
        the app data is cleared, or the app is uninstalled. An email you send to
        the publisher may be retained only as long as reasonably necessary to
        answer the request, maintain appropriate records, and meet legal
        obligations.
      </p>
      <p>
        Google and Apple control retention and deletion for information handled
        by AdMob, Google Play Games, and Game Center. Use the privacy and account
        controls supplied by the relevant provider to manage that information.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Your choices and rights</h2>
      <ul>
        {slimefallArcadeLegal.choices.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
      </ul>
      <p>
        Depending on where you live, privacy law may provide additional rights
        concerning access, correction, deletion, restriction, objection, or
        appeal. Contact the publisher to exercise a right concerning information
        the publisher controls. Requests involving a Google or Apple service
        should be directed to that provider.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Security and international processing</h2>
      <p>
        Reasonable measures are used to limit the information handled directly
        by the publisher. No storage or transmission method can be guaranteed to
        be completely secure. Google and Apple may process information in
        countries other than your own, subject to their policies and applicable
        legal safeguards.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>General audience</h2>
      <p>
        {slimefallArcadeLegal.appName} is a simple, inoffensive game for a general
        audience and is not specifically designed or marketed as a
        child-directed service. The publisher does not knowingly request names,
        email addresses, or other personal details from players through the
        game. Platform providers may apply age-appropriate account, advertising,
        and privacy protections under their own policies.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        This policy may be updated when the game, its service providers, or legal
        requirements change. The effective date at the top of the page will be
        revised when an updated policy is published.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Send questions or privacy requests to
        <a href={supportHref}>{slimefallArcadeLegal.supportEmail}</a>.
      </p>
    </article>

    <Fragment slot="aside">
      <article class="legal-aside-card">
        <h2>Services in scope</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Device-local game storage</li>
          <li>Google Play Games on Android</li>
          <li>Apple Game Center on Apple devices</li>
          <li>Google AdMob advertising</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="legal-aside-card">
        <h2>Not used by the publisher</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>No first-party player accounts</li>
          <li>No publisher-operated cloud save</li>
          <li>No first-party analytics SDK</li>
          <li>No location, camera, or microphone access</li>
          <li>No in-app purchases in the current release</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="legal-aside-card">
        <h2>Provider policies</h2>
        <ul>
          {
            slimefallArcadeLegal.thirdPartyLinks.map((link) => (
              <li><a href={link.href}>{link.label}</a></li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>
      </article>
    </Fragment>
  </LegalPageShell>
</BaseLayout>
